    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  The population and governments of many countries are losing interest in the SARS-CoV-2 infection, the number of tests and the number of new cases detected is sharply decreasing. To compare the accumulated numbers\n                  <jats:italic>CC</jats:italic>\n                  of cases and deaths\n                  <jats:italic>DC</jats:italic>\n                  per million and to answer the question why the less vaccinated Africa has accumulated 36 times lower\n                  <jats:italic>CC</jats:italic>\n                  values and 15 times lower\n                  <jats:italic>DC</jats:italic>\n                  values than Europe, simple statistical analysis have been performed.\n                  <jats:italic>CC</jats:italic>\n                  and\n                  <jats:italic>DC</jats:italic>\n                  values demonstrated rather strong correlation with the median age of populations. One-year increment in the median year yields 12-18 thousand increase in\n                  <jats:italic>CC</jats:italic>\n                  values and 52-83 increase in\n                  <jats:italic>DC</jats:italic>\n                  values. Zero-COVID countries succeed to have much lower numbers of deaths per capita and case fatality ratios\n                  <jats:italic>DC/CC</jats:italic>\n                  .\n                </jats:p>",
